VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DES fast sky-map instrument distribution - 11.6 eV (E1) using averaged even/odd steps
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Az bin: sector ind=00 looks "after" (spin-phase) Sun, ..., sector ind=31 looks "before" Sun dir.  Head field-of-view: pixel index=00 looks to zenith, ..., pixel index=15 looks to nadir.  FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31.  Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DES vector of data-quality indicators at fast survey-start time - 32-bit error flags
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of zero signifies no quality errors. For non-zero values: Bit-0 = manually flagged interval, Bit-1 = overcounting/saturation effects likely present in skymap

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DES compression lossless/lossy indicator at survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DES compression loss indicator, 0=lossless, 1=lossy

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DES Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) count at fast survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase counts range over [0000, 5759] cnts.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase count indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS3 FPI/DES Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) angle at fast survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase angles range over [0, 360) deg.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase angle indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI azimuth sector index used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Azimuth bin: sector index=00 looks "after" (spin-phase) Sun, ..., sector index=31 looks "before" Sun dir.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DES fast survey average f1 count values
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Average f1-count level as a function of energy

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI azimuth sector label used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Azimuth bin: "sector00" looks after Sun, ..., "sector31" looks before Sun dir.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI pixel index used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Head field-of-view: pixel index=00 looks to zenith, ..., pixel index=15 looks to nadir.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI pixel label used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Head field-of-view: "pixel00" looks to zenith, ..., "pixel15" looks to nadir.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI energy-bin index used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31.  Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI energy-bin label used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31.  Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS FPI/DES fast survey sky-map constant zenith angles
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Pixel zenith angles

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DES fast survey sky-map zenith angle bin deltas
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Pixel zenith angle deltas

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DES fast survey sky-map energies
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Geometric mean of parity 0 and parity 1 energies in the 64-step FPI energy table

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS3 FPI/DES fast survey sky-map delta energies
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Note that the deltas are provided to indicate that FPI is reporting the energy bin centers. These do not necessarily reflect the energy bandwidth that is sampled by FPI at a given energy step.
